  "subject": "Fix RTD build: migrate from sphinxcontrib-needs to sphinx-needs",
  "commit_message": "Fix RTD build: migrate from sphinxcontrib-needs to sphinx-needs\n\nThe abandoned sphinxcontrib-needs 0.7.9 package has two incompatibilities\nthat break the Read the Docs build:\n\n1. Imports pkg_resources (removed from setuptools>=82)\n2. Imports sphinx.util.status_iterator (removed from Sphinx 8.2+)\n\nRTD upgrades both setuptools and Sphinx to latest versions before\nprocessing requirements-docs.txt, so pinning upper bounds is fragile\nand requires ongoing maintenance as new versions are released.\n\nReplace sphinxcontrib-needs with its maintained successor sphinx-needs\n(same maintainers at useblocks, different package name). sphinx-needs\n7.0.0 is compatible with modern setuptools and Sphinx 9.x, eliminating\nboth issues permanently.\n\nThe extension name in conf.py changes from 'sphinxcontrib.needs' to\n'sphinx_needs'. All existing conf.py settings (needs_extra_options,\nneeds_id_regex, needs_id_required, needs_title_optional) and RST\ndirectives (.. req::, etc.) are fully backward compatible.\n\nWith this change, the setuptools<81 and sphinx<9 upper bounds added by\nthe previous fix (143563) are no longer needed and are removed.\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nChange-Id: Ieee64249e94d0c76f46d6b9f1b56691c2036f8f6\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
